            "type": "text",
            "text": "Error Detection in Agentic Pipelines"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Self-correction begins with error detection \u2014 identifying that something is wrong before deciding how to fix it. Errors fall into three categories: structural errors (wrong type, missing field, malformed JSON), semantic errors (factually wrong, contradicts goal), and execution errors (tool call failed, exception raised). Each category calls for a different detection strategy."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Layered Error Detection Pipeline",
          "title": ""
        }
